was established by directive of the Dean of Faculty to more fully integrate student scholarly inquiry into the VMI experience  The Cadet Investment Group The Cadet Investment Group  CIG  was founded in 1986 with  200 000 provided by the VMI Foundation  Cadet Internships Beginning summer 2007  the department has instituted an  internship for credit  program  The Class of 2005 In May of 2005  29 cadets graduated with an ECBU degree  23 responded to a recent survey  Here s what they re up to  Cadet Field Trip On Friday  23 March  2007  18 enthusiastic ECBU majors traveled to Richmond to tour the Richmond Federal Reserve Bank and to talk with Ray Owens  an economist working for the Fed  Cadet Awards The Annual ODE Banquet to honor our top cadets was held on March 27th  Hinman Award Winner What began as a summer undergraduate research opportunity in 2005  concluded with the Wilbur S  Hinman  Jr   06 Research Award for Cadet Michael Canning  07  at this year s Institute Awards  Stay Connected to ECBU Please let us know what you ve been up to by emailing us at ECBUnewsletter vmi edu  If you are interested in hosting a field trip  accepting an intern  speaking to our cadets or helping out in any way at all  just let us know  Even if you have nothing to report  send an email to let us know that you want to be on our email list  Spring 2007 Newsletter  AACSB Accreditation  Field Test BU  Mission Statement  New Faculty Faces  New Book Released  Faculty Research  Speakers  Engineering Initiative  Cadet Research  Cadet Investment Group  Cadet Internships  Class of 2005  Cadet Field Trip  Cadet Awards  Hinman Award  Stay Connected  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong ap