t  New Book Released Colonel Stewart W  Husted  The John and Jane Roberts Chair of Free Enterprise Business  has recently written a book  George C  Marshall  Rubrics of Leadership  Faculty Research Our faculty have been hard at work publishing research in academic journals as well as presenting their research at various conferences around the country and the world  Speakers In the Spring semester  we were fortunate to have three  distinguished speakers address to our cadets  We appreciate the time they ve taken to address our cadets  Engineering Entrepreneurship Initiative The Engineering Entrepreneurship Initiative  EEI  is a new program developed to give Entrepreneurship students the opportunity to write business plans for patented intellectual property  Cadet Research The VMI Undergraduate Research Initiative  URI  was established by directive of the Dean of Faculty to more fully integrate student scholarly inquiry into the VMI experience  The Cadet Investment Group The Cadet Investment Group  CIG  was founded in 1986 with  200 000 provided by the VMI Foundation  Cadet Internships Beginning summer 2007  the department has instituted an  internship for credit  program  The Class of 2005 In May of 2005  29 cadets graduated with an ECBU degree  23 responded to a recent survey  Here s what they re up to  Cadet Field Trip On Friday  23 March  2007  18 enthusiastic ECBU majors traveled to Richmond to tour the Richmond Federal Reserve Bank and to talk with Ray Owens  an economist working for the Fed  Cadet Awards The Annual ODE Banquet to honor our top cadets was held on March 27th  Hinman Award Winner What began as a summer undergraduate research opportunity in 2005  concluded with the Wilbur S  Hinman  Jr   06 Research Award for Cadet Michael Canning  07  at this year s Institute Awards  Stay Connected to ECBU Please let us know what you ve been up to by emailing us at ECBUnewsletter vmi edu  If you are interested in hosting a field trip  accepting an intern  speaking to our cadets or helping out in any way at all  just let us know  Even if you have nothing to report  send an email to let us know that you want to be on our email list  Spring 2007 Newsletter  AACSB Accreditation  Field Test BU  Mission Statement  New Faculty Faces  New Book Released  Faculty Research  Speakers  Engineering Initiative  Cadet Research  Cadet Investment Group  Cadet Internships  Class of 2005  Cadet Field Trip  Cadet Awards  Hinman Award  Stay Connected Home   Academics   Areas of Study   Social Science   Economics   Business   Economics Newsletter   Spring 2007 Home   Academics   Areas of Study   Social Science   Economics   Business   Economics Newsletter   Spring 2007 Home Academics Areas of Study Social Science Economics   Business      Economics Newsletter Spring 2007 Greetings alumni and friends  Welcome to the 1st edition of the department s newsletter  We trust you will enjoy reading about the exciting things we are doing  Just click on the topic headings for the full story  With warm regards  Floyd H  Duncan  Col  Department Chairman AACSB Accreditation In August 2004  with support and encouragement from the dean and superintendent  the Department of Economics and Business submitted an accreditation plan to AACSB International  the Association to Advance Collegiate Schools of Business  The Major Field Test in Business For the second year in a row  the graduating first class economics and business majors scored in the top 5  of all schools taking the Educational Testing Service s Major Field Test Business  Our Mission Statement Perhaps the most important component of the department s drive toward accreditation was the development of a mission statement  New Faculty Faces The department of Economics and Business has gone through an expansion Here are some of the new faces in the department  New Book Released Colonel Stewart W  Husted  The John and Jane Roberts Chair of Free Enterprise Business  has recently written a book  George C  Marshall 